\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces  Elastic failure with internal bridge formation. The bridge ruptures near the surface layer (marked), exposing a fluid core that elongates and breaks again. Time values indicate progression from the start of the drawing process. Solution is composed of 44\% zein and 90\% ethanol. The solution is drawn with an acceleration of 1000 mm/s$^2$ until a maximum draw velocity of 10 mm/s is reached over a distance of 100 mm. }}{10}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:skin}{{4}{10}{Elastic failure with internal bridge formation. The bridge ruptures near the surface layer (marked), exposing a fluid core that elongates and breaks again. Time values indicate progression from the start of the drawing process. Solution is composed of 44\% zein and 90\% ethanol. The solution is drawn with an acceleration of 1000 mm/s$^2$ until a maximum draw velocity of 10 mm/s is reached over a distance of 100 mm}{figure.caption.5}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces  Collective diameter evolution during fiber drawing process over $N$ trials for (A) the capillary failure mode (41\% zein for $N=15$), (B) the successful fiber formation mode (44\% zein for $N=25$), and (C) the elastic failure mode (48\% zein for $N=27$). Solid lines show the mean diameter for $N$ trials. Shaded regions indicate one standard deviation from the mean. Measurements prior to $t=0.1$~s are excluded due to the pin occupying the camera's field of view. }}{11}{figure.caption.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:diameter_trace}{{5}{11}{Collective diameter evolution during fiber drawing process over $N$ trials for (A) the capillary failure mode (41\% zein for $N=15$), (B) the successful fiber formation mode (44\% zein for $N=25$), and (C) the elastic failure mode (48\% zein for $N=27$). Solid lines show the mean diameter for $N$ trials. Shaded regions indicate one standard deviation from the mean. Measurements prior to $t=0.1$~s are excluded due to the pin occupying the camera's field of view}{figure.caption.6}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces  Final liquid bridge diameters as a function of zein concentration for solutions containing (A) 70\%, (B) 80\%, and (C) 90\% ethanol. Box plots are grouped by failure mode: success (s, green), elastic failure (e, orange), and capillary failure (c, blue). Medians are shown as solid black lines, outliers are plotted as white dots. Box transparency indicates the number of trials, as shown in the shading scale included in panel (A). A red dashed vertical line marks a reference viscosity of 10~Pa$\cdot $s for comparison across all conditions. }}{11}{figure.caption.7}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:diameter_by_etoh}{{6}{11}{Final liquid bridge diameters as a function of zein concentration for solutions containing (A) 70\%, (B) 80\%, and (C) 90\% ethanol. Box plots are grouped by failure mode: success (s, green), elastic failure (e, orange), and capillary failure (c, blue). Medians are shown as solid black lines, outliers are plotted as white dots. Box transparency indicates the number of trials, as shown in the shading scale included in panel (A). A red dashed vertical line marks a reference viscosity of 10~Pa$\cdot $s for comparison across all conditions}{figure.caption.7}{}}
